# Python Log Analyzer

A beginner-friendly Apache log analyzer built as part of my cybersecurity Python learning path. This tool parses web server logs, identifies failed HTTP requests, and summarizes suspicious IP activity — core skills for SOC analyst work.

---

## What It Does

- Parses Apache-style web server log files
- Flags failed requests by HTTP status code (401, 403, 404, 500)
- Counts failed attempts per IP address and ranks by frequency
- Displays a detailed event log and summary report

---

## Why I Built This

As part of my transition into cybersecurity, I wanted to build practical tools that reflect real SOC analyst workflows. Log parsing and identifying brute force patterns are daily tasks in a SOC environment. This project helped me understand:

- File I/O in Python
- Regular expressions (regex) for log parsing
- Data structures (`defaultdict`, lists, tuples)
- Clean code practices (functions, docstrings, error handling)

